						<div class="postbody">Since this topic came up at #nesdev, and I was a bit bored, I wrote a small Python script to generate a visual representation of the PPU signal layout:<br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<img src="./download/file.php?id=2288" alt="nes-ppu-render-layout.png" /><br />
			<span class="gensmall">nes-ppu-render-layout.png [ 939 Bytes | Viewed 371 times ]</span>
		

		<br />
	</div><br />Here's the same image shifted right 70 pixels, so that the front porch is at the left side of the image (PPU counter 0,0 is at 70,0 in image):<br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<img src="./download/file.php?id=2290" alt="nes-ppu-render-layout-shifted70.png" /><br />
			<span class="gensmall">nes-ppu-render-layout-shifted70.png [ 923 Bytes | Viewed 371 times ]</span>
		

		<br />
	</div><br />Key: blue = border, red = active, light gray = sync, green = colorburst, dark gray = &quot;pulse&quot; (in wiki table terminology)<br /><br />Images are based on info from: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php?title=NTSC_video&amp;oldid=9006">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php?titl ... oldid=9006</a><!-- m -->. If you notice any mistakes, lmk.</div>

					
